title: Entry Level Data Engineer
description:
About Revature:

This is an excellent opportunity to launch your career in the tech industry. Revature has started more than 15,000 tech careers, providing comprehensive training to prepare new employees for client projects. No prior technical experience is required—we provide employer-paid training designed to help you succeed.

About the Role:

Data Engineers build and maintain the infrastructure that enables organizations to collect, store, and analyze data efficiently. As an Entry-Level Data Engineer at Revature, you will gain:

Benefits Of Working As a Data Engineer
• Strong Foundation in Data Infrastructure
• Hands-on experience with tools and systems that power data pipelines, cloud environments, and analytics platforms.
• Exposure to Scalable Technologies
• Learn and work with technologies such as SQL, Python, Spark, and major cloud services (AWS, Azure, Google Cloud Platform).
• Cross-Functional Collaboration
• Collaborate with data analysts, data scientists, engineers, and product teams.
• Career Growth & Specialization
• Build a pathway toward advanced roles in data engineering, analytics, cloud engineering, or machine learning.

What We’re Looking For
• Bachelor's degree or higher
• Legally authorized to work in the U.S. without current or future sponsorship
• Strong desire to learn programming (no prior professional experience required)
• Natural problem-solving ability with strong communication and interpersonal skills

Benefits Of Joining Revature As An Entry-Level Data Engineer
• Start a tech career with no prior experience required
• Competitive salary
• Paid time off (PTO)
• 401(k)
• Mentorship programs
• Experience working with the largest companies in the U.S.
• Career acceleration:
• 72% of Revature alumni receive an additional promotion
• 92% see significant salary increases after launching their Revature tech career

Equal Opportunity Employer:

Revature (“Company”) is an equal opportunity employer. We will extend equal opportunity to all individuals without regard to race, religion, color, sex, pregnancy, childbirth or related medical conditions, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, disability, age, genetic information, marital status, veteran status, or any other status protected under applicable federal, state, or local laws. If you require accommodation to work, based on any of these protected factors, please notify the Human Resources Department, and the Company will evaluate the request and provide accommodation in accordance with applicable law.

title: Data Science Intern
description:
Join us as a Data Science Intern and work on real-world medical data science use cases with a strong focus on computer vision. In this full-time, six-month internship, you'll gain hands-on experience with tools like YOLOv8 and Azure while contributing to projects involving image preprocessing, model training, and evaluation. You'll collaborate with data scientists and clinical experts to help build and refine AI-driven imaging models. If you're passionate about Python, deep learning, and solving meaningful problems, we encourage you to explore this opportunity.

Position Summary

This individual will participate in a full-time internship program, working 35-40 hours per week for a period of approximately six months. The intern will engage in data science projects with a focus on computer vision. They will gain exposure to real-world medical data science use cases, utilize cutting-edge AI computer vision technologies such as Yolov8, and have an opportunity to work in a cloud-based Azure environment. Projects may include data preprocessing, model training, evaluation, deployment, data visualization, and other assigned tasks.

Essential Functions And Job Responsibilities

The intern may be assigned a wide variety of tasks depending on department workload and priorities, as well as the individual’s strengths, skillset, and background. Tasks may vary from routine work to complex, multi-step projects. Specific responsibilities include:
• Solving real-world dental imaging and X-ray analysis challenges using advanced computer vision and AI technologies
• Owning and contributing to the full computer vision pipeline for dental X-ray analysis, including image extraction, preprocessing, normalization, and classification
• Designing, training, evaluating, and deploying deep learning models for object detection, instance segmentation, and keypoint detection (e.g., YOLOv8-based models)
• Performing tooth detection, segmentation, tooth number attribution, and anatomical landmark detection
• Converting pixel-level model outputs into real-world clinical measurements (e.g., bone loss in millimeters)
• Building scalable inference pipelines, model orchestration workflows, and visualization/QA tooling
• Managing and supporting data labeling workflows, including defining label schemas, QA processes, and gold-standard datasets
• Collaborating closely with dental subject matter experts, hygienists, and technical team members to ensure clinical relevance and project success
• Visualizing data, model outputs, and results and presenting findings to technical and business stakeholders

Qualifications
• Pursuing or completed bachelor’s degree from an accredited college required; degrees in computer science, data science, engineering, mathematics, or related fields preferred
• Experience in Python and PyTorch or other modern deep learning frameworks
• Strong experience with computer vision techniques, including image classification, instance segmentation, and keypoint/landmark detection
• Hands-on experience with YOLOv8 for detection, segmentation, and/or keypoint modeling strongly preferred
• Familiarity with data labeling tools and workflows (e.g., V7 or similar platforms) a strong plus
• Experience translating model predictions into deterministic, rule-based or guideline-driven logic
• Ability to independently own systems and projects end-to-end
• Attention to detail, accuracy, and strong problem-solving skills. Strong verbal and written communication skills
• Motivated with a strong interest in learning new skills and tasks
• Ability to work independently and in a team environment
• Ability to multi-task and work under tight deadlines
• Proven subscription to the company’s core values of integrity, trust and respect, innovation, stewardship, excellence, and celebration

Work Conditions

General office working conditions which may require sitting for extended periods of time

Physical Requirements

The physical demands described here are representative of those that must be met by an employee to successfully perform the essential functions of this job. Reasonable accommodations may be made to enable individuals with disabilities to perform the essential functions.

Specific vision abilities require the ability to focus distant and near objects clearly. While performing the duties of this job, the employee is regularly required to sit, talk and hear. The employee is frequently required to use hands and arms to handle, feel and reach as well as operate a personal computer.

Disclaimer

This job description is designed to provide a general overview of the requirements of the job and does not entail a comprehensive listing of activities, duties, or responsibilities that will be required. The organization reserves the right to modify this job description at any time; including assigning or reassigning job duties or eliminating the position at any time.

Equal Opportunity Employer

This employer is required to notify all applicants of their rights pursuant to federal employment laws. For further information, please review the Know Your Rights notice from the Department of Labor.

title: Software Developer (Entry Level)
description:
Please note that this position is based on our campus in Madison, WI, and requires relocation to the area. We recruit nationally and provide financial relocation assistance.

Code that saves lives.

As a software developer at Epic, you’ll write software that impacts the lives of 325 million patients around the world. Working in your own office, surrounded by thousands of high-caliber developers, you’ll use modern development methodologies and employ user-centered design, analytics, and machine learning tools to drive innovation in healthcare. Using leading-edge technologies and languages like JS, TS, and C#, you’ll invent better ways to reduce medical errors, streamline record sharing between hospitals, and provide the quality of care a patient deserves. Learn more about our team at https://careers.epic.com/jobs/softwaredevelopment/.

Write software for the most innovative health systems on the planet.

The top-ranked health systems in U.S. News and World Report are Epic customers. Our community includes major systems like the Mayo Clinic, Johns Hopkins, Cleveland Clinic, and Kaiser Permanente, as well as leading academic medical centers at the University of Wisconsin, University of Michigan, University of California, University of Texas, The Ohio State University, and many more.

Live affordably in a city known for its rising tech talent.

Epic is located just outside Madison, Wisconsin, the second fastest growing market for tech talent in the United States and home to the state capital and the University of Wisconsin. Madison, a city surrounded by water, has received accolades for being the greenest city in America (NerdWallet), the best city for renters (SmartAsset), the fittest city in America (Fitbit), and the third best metro in the US for young professionals (Forbes Advisor).

More than just important work.

Our uniquely themed campus was designed to heighten your ability to get stuff done in your office, a conference room, or by the fireplace in a comfy chair. All meals are restaurant-quality but cost only a few dollars, and they’re prepared by a team comprised of kitchen talent from restaurants around the country. And, after five years here, you’ll earn a four-week sabbatical anywhere in the world. Staff have kayaked in Patagonia, attended a Beyoncé concert in Ireland, built a library in Tanzania, and run a marathon in Antarctica.

We offer comprehensive benefits to keep you healthy and happy as you grow in your life and career, and your merit-based compensation will reflect the impact your work has on the company and our customers. You'll also be eligible for annual raises and bonuses, as well as stock grants, which give you an even greater stake in the success of Epic and our customers. Healthcare is global, and building the best ideas from around the world into Epic software is a point of pride. As an Equal Opportunity Employer, we know that inclusive teams design software that supports the delivery of quality care for all patients, so diversity, equity, and inclusion are written into our principles. Please see our full non-discrimination statement at https://careers.epic.com/EEO.
• Relocation to the Madison, WI area (Reimbursed)
• BS/BA or greater in Computer Science, Mathematics, Software Engineering, Computer Engineering, or a related field
• A history of academic excellence or professional success
• Eligible to work in the United States without visa sponsorship (persons with appropriate qualifications and eligible for TN status under NAFTA may apply)
• COVID-19 vaccination

title: Summer Engineering Internship
description:
About General Galactic

General Galactic designs, develops, and builds advanced spacecraft to create the Galactic Armada, a fleet of spacecraft behind an orbital logistics network. Led by former SpaceX, Varda, and Relativity engineers, our vision is to expand access to high-energy orbits across LEO, MEO, GEO, and cislunar space with our water-electrolysis based Genesis propulsion technology.

Based in El Segundo, California, we are developing paradigm-shifting propulsion systems that tightly integrate into the highest mobility satellite platform, ever. Our first orbital mission will fly in 2026.

Internship Overview

As a Summer Engineering Intern, you will work directly with General Galactic’s founders and technical team on flight-critical projects. Interns are treated as engineers in their own right and are expected to take real ownership of scoped projects that result in new hardware, actionable test data, or flight-ready components.

What You’ll Work On

Depending on your background, interests, and the company’s program needs, you may work in one or more of the following areas:
• Chemical propulsion
• Electric propulsion
• Electrolysis & energy systems
• Avionics & electrical hardware
• Fluids, valves, and pressure systems
• Flight structures, mechanisms, and integration

Responsibilities may include a subset of the following, tailored to your strengths:
• Propulsion system integration, testing, and performance characterization
• Development of avionics hardware, power electronics, sensors, and harnessing
• Development of electrolysis systems, fluid handling, and gas management hardware
• Design and build test fixtures, pressure systems, and experimental hardware
• Support structural design, CAD, fabrication, and hardware assembly
• Execute test campaigns, analyze results, troubleshoot failures, and iterate designs
• Work across disciplines to mature systems toward flight readiness

You will be expected to move quickly, reason from first principles, and operate effectively with incomplete information.

Basic Qualifications
• Currently pursuing a BS or MS in Aerospace/Mechanical/Electrical/Chemical Engineering, Engineering Physics, or a related field
• Strong fundamentals in engineering analysis and physical systems
• Hands-on experience with hardware, fabrication, or experimental systems
• Strong communication skills in a collaborative team environment
• Ability to work full-time on-site in Los Angeles for the duration of the internship

Preferred Qualifications

(Not required—strong candidates may have experience in some, not all, areas)
• Experience with CAD tools (e.g., SolidWorks, Onshape, NX, Fusion)
• Experience with electronics, PCB layout, power electronics, or avionics hardware
• Experience with propulsion systems, fluids, pressure vessels, or thermal systems
• Experience building, assembling, or debugging physical hardware
• Experience with lab equipment, test stands, or instrumentation
• Prior involvement in rocketry, spacecraft, research labs, or hands-on engineering teams

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This position requires access to information protected under US export control laws, including the International Traffic in Arms Regulations and/or the Export Administration Regulations. As such, US person status (including US citizens, U.S. permanent residents, individuals granted U.S. asylum status, or individuals admitted in U.S. refugee status) is a required qualification for this position.
